<paragraph blockId="12.[163,777,447,499]" pageId="12">
<emphasis box="[163,300,447,468]" italics="true" pageId="12">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name is derived from the Greek ζοφερος, gloomy, referring to the dark mesoscutum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[163,780,540,868]" pageId="12">
<emphasis box="[163,291,541,562]" italics="true" pageId="12">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen et al., 2009" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qinlingensis">
<emphasis box="[597,613,540,561]" italics="true" pageId="12">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[630,778,540,561]" italics="true" pageId="12">qinlingensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chen XP &amp; Gao JJ &amp; Chen HW" box="[163,367,571,593]" pageId="12" pagination="1909 - 1927" refId="ref11498" refString="Chen XP, Gao JJ, Chen HW. 2009. The Stegana shirozui species group (Diptera, Drosophilidae) from East Asia. Journal of Natural History 43: 1909 - 1927." type="journal article" year="2009">
Chen 
<emphasis box="[234,294,571,592]" italics="true" pageId="12">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<quantity box="[310,367,571,592]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.10286" pageId="12" unit="in" value="2009.0">2009</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in hypandrium having numerous, small, serrated processes on the flaps (
<figureCitation box="[606,719,601,623]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="11.[145,223,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[306,1263,1115,1777]" captionTargetId="figure-475@11.[303,1266,1112,1780]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 8. Stegana (Steganina) zopheria sp. nov. A. epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); B. surstylus (ventral view); C, D. hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. gonopods (ventral and lateral views). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." pageId="12">Fig. 8C, D</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished from the latter species by having the opening of aedeagus nearly rhombic in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[240,330,693,715]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="11.[145,223,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[306,1263,1115,1777]" captionTargetId="figure-475@11.[303,1266,1112,1780]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 8. Stegana (Steganina) zopheria sp. nov. A. epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); B. surstylus (ventral view); C, D. hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. gonopods (ventral and lateral views). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." pageId="12">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
); the dorsal projection of gonopods rod-like, strongly recurved ventrad (
<figureCitation box="[607,727,724,746]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="11.[145,223,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[306,1263,1115,1777]" captionTargetId="figure-475@11.[303,1266,1112,1780]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 8. Stegana (Steganina) zopheria sp. nov. A. epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); B. surstylus (ventral view); C, D. hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. gonopods (ventral and lateral views). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." pageId="12">Fig. 8C, D</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName box="[163,339,755,776]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qinlingensis">
<emphasis box="[163,179,755,776]" italics="true" pageId="12">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[195,339,755,776]" italics="true" pageId="12">qinlingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: opening of aedeagus is narrow, slitlike in ventral view (as fig. 
<quantity box="[493,552,785,807]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.906" pageId="12" unit="in" value="39.0">39 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Chen XP &amp; Gao JJ &amp; Chen HW" box="[562,763,785,807]" pageId="12" pagination="1909 - 1927" refId="ref11498" refString="Chen XP, Gao JJ, Chen HW. 2009. The Stegana shirozui species group (Diptera, Drosophilidae) from East Asia. Journal of Natural History 43: 1909 - 1927." type="journal article" year="2009">
Chen 
<emphasis box="[632,692,785,807]" italics="true" pageId="12">et al.</emphasis>
, 2009
</bibRefCitation>
); dorsal projection of gonopods posteriorly protruded (as figs 40, 41 in 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen XP &amp; Gao JJ &amp; Chen HW" box="[314,504,846,868]" pageId="12" pagination="1909 - 1927" refId="ref11498" refString="Chen XP, Gao JJ, Chen HW. 2009. The Stegana shirozui species group (Diptera, Drosophilidae) from East Asia. Journal of Natural History 43: 1909 - 1927." type="journal article" year="2009">
Chen 
<emphasis box="[381,437,846,868]" italics="true" pageId="12">et al.</emphasis>
, 2009
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
