<paragraph blockId="12.[163,303,1381,1404]" box="[163,303,1381,1404]" pageId="12">
<emphasis box="[163,303,1381,1404]" italics="true" pageId="12">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[163,779,1421,1535]" pageId="12">
<emphasis box="[163,448,1421,1442]" italics="true" pageId="12">Male and female. Head:</emphasis>
Frons brown, with a black band below. First flagellomere yellow, black on distal quarter, with black pubescence along margin. Clypeus brown. Palpus yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[163,778,1568,1682]" pageId="12">
<emphasis box="[163,401,1568,1590]" italics="true" pageId="12">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[262,386,1568,1590]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[163,241,1019,1041]" captionTargetBox="[170,775,195,979]" captionTargetId="figure-647@8.[167,775,195,979]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Habitus ofholotypes.A,B.Stegana (Steganina) alianya sp. nov.; C, D. Stegana (Steganina) diodonta sp. nov.; E, F. Stegana (Steganina) zebromyia sp. nov.; G, H. Stegana (Steganina) zopheria sp. nov." pageId="12">Figs 4G, H</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
Mesoscutum dark brown (male) to black (female), medially and laterally with yellow longitudinal strips. Scutellum dark brown in male, black in female.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[163,779,1723,1898]" pageId="12">
<emphasis box="[163,489,1723,1744]" italics="true" pageId="12">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[396,471,1723,1744]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="11.[145,223,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[306,1263,1115,1777]" captionTargetId="figure-475@11.[303,1266,1112,1780]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 8. Stegana (Steganina) zopheria sp. nov. A. epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); B. surstylus (ventral view); C, D. hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. gonopods (ventral and lateral views). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." pageId="12">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
Epandrium ventrally protruded. Cercus lacking pubescence. Surstylus submedially with ca. seven prensisetae. Aedeagus dorsolaterally with several serrated processes in lateral view. Paramere with ca. three sensilla. Gonopods medially protruded in ventral view.
</paragraph>
